						Concerned about your privacy?
					.arrange_concern
						%p
							You have full control over your privacy on PLUS/BE.
							%br
							None of your data will be shared with other social networking platforms (eg. Facebook, Twitter, etc) or organisations, without your prior consent.
							%br
							The team behind PLUS/BE are committed to delivering an experience that is user-friendly and easy-to-use. 
						%p
							%h3
								To register to for the first-time on PLUS/BE, you have two options:
							%ul.floatleft.concern-list
								%li
									You can Sign Up with Social+ Networks to set-up and regularly login of your new PLUS/BE account with a few clicks of a mouse; or,
								%li
									You can Sign Up with Email and type in your email contact details and an email will sent to you confirming your new account.  
						%br
						%p
							Regardless of the way that you register for the first time, all PLUS/BE users must agree to the purpose, values, terms of use and codes of conduct that are explained at the end of the registration process. All users are able to use their full name or choose a user name alias for their profile. In addition, all users will control over the privacy settings of their profile, and can choose to remain anonymous.
						%p
							PLUS/BE Community Managers are on-duty to ensure that web-app all users adhere to the terms of use and codes of conduct. The Community Manager are also there to facilitate the questions and answers among the users and refer users to assistance if they are in need.
						%p
							%h3
								To
								%u
									= link_to "Sign Up with Social+ Networks", social_experimental_index_path(:via=>"networks") 
						%br
						%p
							New users are offered the choice of using their existing social networking, Gmail or Yahoo! Accounts set-up a new account on PLUS/BE, making the registration process as easy as a few mouse clicks. 
							%br
							This also enables the user to use their existing social networking account as a key to re-login after registering for the first time.
							%br
							If you choose to use your social networking account to register on PLUS/BE, our server will reference your name and email address data from your social networking profile so that it can be inputted automatically into your new PLUS/BE profile. This is a one-way data transaction. There is no notification on your social networking profile (or among your friends) about your registration on PLUS/BE.
						%p
							%h3
								To
								%u
									= link_to " Sign Up with Email", social_experimental_index_path(:via=>"email")
						%br
						%p
							You can register on PLUS/BE by typing in your email contact details and other basic information. Once you submit your contact details, a confirmation email will be sent to your designated address and you can proceed with accessing PLUS/BE.
							%br
							To re-login in once you have registered, you will need type in your email address and password.
